<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>

    <meta charset="UTF-8">

    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

    <title>FAQ</title>

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">

</head>

<body>

<header class="main-header">
    <a href="/" class="logo-link">
        <img src="/images/logo.png" class="logo" alt="QR-Found">
    </a>
</header>

<div class="container">

    <div class="faq-title">

        Frequently Asked Questions

    </div>

    <div class="accordion">

    <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header">Is QR-Found free to use? <span class="icon">▼</span></div>
        <div class="accordion-content">Yes! Creating and using digital QR codes for your items is completely free.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header">How does it work? <span class="icon">▼</span></div>
        <div class="accordion-content">You create a tag with your contact info, download it, and attach it to your item. If someone finds it, they scan the QR and contact you.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header">What happens if I lose the qr code? <span class="icon">▼</span></div>
        <div class="accordion-content">Since we do not store your data permanently, you will need to create a new QR code. It takes less than a minute.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header">Do I need a special app to scan the code? <span class="icon">▼</span></div>
        <div class="accordion-content">No! Any modern smartphone camera can scan QR codes automatically.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header">Can I edit my info after printing the QR? <span class="icon">▼</span></div>
        <div class="accordion-content">No, the data is encoded into the QR for security reasons. If you need changes, just generate a new one.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header">Which format is better: PDF or PNG? <span class="icon">▼</span></div>
        <div class="accordion-content">PDF is best for printing at home in high quality. PNG is better for digital use or custom designs.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header">Where should I attach the QR code? <span class="icon">▼</span></div>
        <div class="accordion-content">Attach it to visible parts of your item like bags, keys, luggage, or electronics so it can be easily scanned.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header">What if someone scans my QR code? <span class="icon">▼</span></div>
        <div class="accordion-content">They will see a simple page with your contact details and can reach you directly via phone, email, or Telegram.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header">Can I use QR-Found for business items? <span class="icon">▼</span></div>
        <div class="accordion-content">Yes, it can be used for personal and business items like equipment, tools, or branded products.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header">Does QR-Found work internationally? <span class="icon">▼</span></div>
        <div class="accordion-content">Yes, QR codes can be scanned anywhere in the world as long as there is internet access.</div>
    </div>

</div>
    <div class="contact-section">

        <div class="contact-title">

            Still have questions?

        </div>

        <div class="contact-text">

            We are always ready to help you.

        </div>

        <a
            href="mailto:support@qrfound.com"
            class="email-btn"
        >

            Write to us:
            support@qrfound.com

        </a>

    </div>

</div>

<footer class="main-footer">

    © 2026 QR-Found

</footer>

<script>

document
.querySelectorAll('.accordion-header')
.forEach(header => {

    header.addEventListener('click', () => {

        header
        .parentElement
        .classList
        .toggle('active');

    });

});

</script>

</body>

</html>